context: And been of good condiciouns therto;
As make it with thise argumentes tough;
O noble wives, ful of heigh prudence
Of songes, ful of armonie,°
Good werkes shal yow noght availe°
Tho bisy wrecches, ful of wo and drede!
With angels ful of cleernesse and of light
Of urine, and our bothe thinges smal°
Of Venus werkes worth his olde sho,°
And cuppes ful of win, and milke and blood
As seith my lord, so make us al good men;
Was in his nedes prest and corageous;
Sixty cubites° long, and seven in brede,°
This king of kinges proud was and elaat,°
Among the Grekes, ful of worthinesse
Upon hir lendes,° ful of many a gore.°
¶Now, good men, God foryeve yow your trespas,°
I fele my limes° stark° and suffisaunt
Upon a bench of turves,° fresh and grene
Forestes, parkes° ful of wilde deer;
Whan thritty tiraunts, ful of cursednesse
For which thise woful maidens, ful of drede
Of Brugges were his hosen° broun
